function clean_column(col::AbstractString)
    return Symbol(lowercase(replace(col, r"^ *| *$" => "", count = Inf), replace(col, r"\s|-" => "_"))
end
```

This function takes a string `col` as input and returns a lowercased, whitespace-stripped version of the column name with hyphens and spaces replaced by underscores. It uses `Symbol` to ensure that the returned value is usable as a Julia identifier.
